Prometheus Metrics Instrumentation
Prerequisites
Basic understanding of Linux command line
Familiarity with HTTP concepts and APIs
Basic knowledge of Python or Go programming
Understanding of system monitoring concepts
Root or sudo access on Linux machine
Learning Objectives
By completing this lab, you will:

Understand Prometheus metrics types and formats
Instrument a service to expose custom metrics
Configure Prometheus to scrape application metrics
Query and visualize metrics to measure system health
Implement best practices for metric naming and labeling
Environment Setup
You will use the Al Nafi provided Linux machine. All tools will be installed during this lab.

System Requirements
Linux machine (Ubuntu 20.04+ or similar)
Minimum 2GB RAM
